      <Desc>1. OPERATED YEAR 2 OF NATE'S PLACE CENTER - SERVED OVER 300 TEENS AND YOUNG ADULTS THROUGH OUR CENTER AND AT SCHOOLS . 2. LED A SERIES OF 3 AND 4-WEEK JOB READINESS WORKSHOPS TO HELP OUR PARTICIPANTS CREATE RESUMES, LEARN HOW TO INTERVIEW AND FIND JOBS. 3. CURRENTLY, THERE ARE APPROXIMATELY 58 PARTICIPANTS ENROLLED AT NATE'S PLACE AT ONE TIME. 4. RECEIVED POSITIVE OUTCOMES: 92% OF PARTICIPANTS REPORT IMPROVED MENTAL HEALTH AS A RESULT OF ATTENDING NATE'S PLACE . 5. RECEIVED POSITIVE OUTCOMES: 94% OF PARTICIPANTS REPORT INCREASED MOTIVATION TO DECREASE SUBSTANCE USE SINCE ATTENDING NATE'S PLACE. 6. BOUGHT A 3RD VAN TO TRANSPORT PARTICIPANTS; PROVIDE APPROX 50 - 65 PICKUPS PER WEEK. 7. SECURED A CONTRACT WITH VENTURA COUNTY BEHAVIORAL HEALTH TO COVER PART OF OUR STAFF WAGES. 8. SERVED TEENS IN 13 SCHOOLS DURING THE 24/25 SCHOOL YEAR. 9. SECURED A CONTRACT TO PROVIDE SERVICES IN THE VENTURA JUVENILE HALL. 10. STARTED OFFERING PICKLEBALL AT CENTER AND AT LOCAL PARK. 11. SEVEN OF OUR PEER SUPPORT RECOVERY COACHES HAVE COMPLETED THE 80 HOUR TRAINING AND 6 ARE CERTIFIED BY THE STATE OF CA.</Desc>
